            </p>
                                    <p class="municipality">
                <strong>Location:</strong>
                Ravensbr&#195;ck, Germany<br />
                            </p>
                            <div>
                Concentration camp for female prisoners. By 1944, Ravensbr&#195;ck and its 34 subcamps had a prisoner population of more than 80,000. Tens of thousands perished there from malnutrition, disease, shootings, phenol injections to the heart, and medical experiments. Six thousand died in its gas chambers.
            </div>
